  "prompt": "Is it risky to install a CNG kit near a car battery?",
  "response": "Installing a CNG (Compressed Natural Gas) kit near a car battery can pose some risks if not done properly. Here are some key considerations:\n\n1. Safety concerns:\n- Potential for electrical sparks\n- Risk of gas leakage\n- Proximity to battery terminals\n- Potential for short circuits\n\n2. Recommended precautions:\n- Maintain adequate distance between battery and CNG kit\n- Use proper insulation and protective barriers\n- Ensure professional installation by certified technicians\n- Follow manufacturer's guidelines\n- Use high-quality components\n- Regular maintenance and inspection\n\n3. Best practices:\n- Install CNG kit away from battery\n- Use flame-retardant materials\n- Ensure proper grounding\n- Use sealed and protected wiring\n- Have periodic safety checks\n\nWhile CNG can be a cost-effective fuel alternative, safety should always be the primary concern during installation and operation.",
